{"type":"message","id":"bcbcd9e1","parentId":"9290fa71","timestamp":"2026-02-27T02:50:23.983Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Fri 2026-02-27 02:50 UTC] Title: Nashville Morning Brief (7:00 AM)Trigger: Run every day at 07:00 America/Chicago.Task: Generate a concise Morning Brief tailored to Nashville, Tennessee, using ONLY these skills: tessie, smart-route, daily-news-digest.Output Structure (clean, brief, actionable):🚗 Tesla Snapshot (Tessie) Current battery % + estimated range Charging status (charging / not charging) + current charge limit Climate status + cabin temp (if available) Any alerts (doors unlocked, windows open, sentry off, low tire pressure, etc.) One clear recommendation if something needs attention <ol start=\"2\">🛣️ Commute & Route (smart-route) Focus: Nashville morning traffic (I-24, I-40, I-65) </ol>Estimated drive time vs. typical for your usual destination (e.g., “Work”) Fastest current route + reason (traffic, incident, closure) If delay > 10 min typical, suggested alternate route If no saved destination, default contextual advice (e.g., “Check I-24 and I-65 traffic”) <ol start=\"3\">🗞️ Nashville News Digest (daily-news-digest) </ol>Top 5 headlines max relevant to Nashville / Middle Tennessee 1–2 sentence summary per headline Highlight anything affecting the morning (weather alerts, road closures, major events) Formatting Rules:Use bullet points; keep it skimmable If a skill fails, mark that section Unavailable with a short reason Keep total length ~250–350 words Conclude with: **✅ Quick Focus: **<one actionable priority for your morning in Nashville>"}],"timestamp":1772160623978}}
